data.name: checkBox2.ToolTip
data.value:
Two points: - If you are making a mod/dlc using W3Editor, you will pack and generate metadata there. So there is no need to do it here.
- Also useful when testing a new version of a texture. Since the 'Cooked' XBM is just a pointer to the texture.cache you can just replace the texture.cache in the installed mod/dlc.

data.name: checkBox3.ToolTip
data.value:
Using this will Skip the Import part of the process! Using this you should already have an 'Uncooked' folder in the mod's directory.
Mostly should be used when creating Icons for DLC items. Put the icons for your mod in: "Uncooked\gameplay\gui_new\icons"

data.name: checkBox1.ToolTip
data.value:
Cook just what you need... You know.. you don't have to cook everything to test one thing... (Just make sure you still have the Uncooked folder of previous time)
When the assets are loaded you can use: CTRL and SHIFT to select one by one or many lines (just like selecting files)
